{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_4","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"rg -n \\\"class Status|SKIPPED|def skip\\\\b|\\\\.skip\\\\(|def next_action|def peek_next|_reserve_goal_promotion|commit_replanned_goals|set_iteration_goals|begin_replanning|active_cycle|PlanPhase\\\" . --glob '\"'!graphify-out/**'\"'\"","aggregated_output":"./README.md:334:The system is a **working prototype past its core-integration milestone**: the current architecture is the cyclic `ProjectPlan` lifecycle (`ProjectPlan → IntentProposal → CycleDraft → GoalContract`, per [ADR-003](docs/decisions/adr-003-cyclic-project-plan-lifecycle.md)) — the conversational reasoner (stub + OpenAI-compatible LLM), catalog-driven runtime resolution, the git-worktree workspace, live SSE, and the full-cycle test walk are all in place, with `mypy` at zero errors and the truth-test suite green. The legacy nine-phase `PlanPhase` machine remains only as a compatibility projection for migrated plans and existing clients (see [`docs/architecture/known-issues.md`](docs/architecture/known-issues.md)). Known operational defects (verified, with reproduction notes) are tracked in [`docs/architecture/known-issues.md`](docs/architecture/known-issues.md) and scheduled in [`ROADMAP.md`](ROADMAP.md) — the two most important: the default lease/timeout combination permits double execution of long tasks under multiple workers, and a poisoned plan can starve a single-worker deployment.\n./CLAUDE.md:38:   - It owns the goal/task tree and is the ONLY caller of `Goal`/`Task` transition methods. **NEVER** mutate goal/task fields from use cases — go through the aggregate's guarded transitions (`start_task`, `complete_task`, `enter_review`, `begin_replanning`, `commit_replanned_goals`, ...). Illegal transitions raise `InvalidTransitionError`.\n./CLAUDE.md:66:**Legacy compatibility (NOT current)**: the nine-phase `PlanPhase` machine (`DISCOVERY → ARCHITECTURE → ENRICHING → AWAITING_REVIEW → RUNNING → REVIEW → DONE`, plus `REPLANNING`/`FAILED`) survives ONLY as a read/transition **compatibility projection** for migrated rows and existing clients (migration 0009 maps phase→status; unbound legacy plans quarantine as BLOCKED with a `project_binding` block, restored via `POST /api/plans/{id}/project-binding`). It is never the authority for a plan with an active cycle — do not describe it as the live model. See [`docs/architecture/known-issues.md`](docs/architecture/known-issues.md).\n./ROADMAP.md:21:exact-revision gate) → active `Cycle`. The old nine-phase `PlanPhase` machine\n./frontend/openapi.json:5526:          \"active_cycle\": {\n./frontend/openapi.json:5643:          \"active_cycle\",\n./frontend/src/styles/tokens.ts:19:import type { PlanPhase, PlanStatus, Status } from '../types/ui';\n./frontend/src/styles/tokens.ts:62:export const PLAN_PHASE: Record<PlanPhase, StatusMeta> = {\n./frontend/src/styles/tokens.ts:75:export const CHAT_PHASES: PlanPhase[] = ['discovery', 'replanning'];\n./docs/history/analyses/2026-07-13-first-live-plan-review.md:87:- PlanPhase.RUNNING documentation: execute goals sequentially;\n./backend/tests/unit/execution/test_execution_safety.py:20:from src.domain.aggregates.planner_orchestrator import Plan, PlanPhase\n./backend/tests/unit/execution/test_execution_safety.py:79:        phase=PlanPhase.RUNNING,\n./backend/tests/unit/execution/test_execution_safety.py:239:    assert stored.active_cycle is not None\n./backend/tests/unit/execution/test_execution_safety.py:240:    assert stored.active_cycle.goals[0].tasks[0].status == Status.DONE\n./backend/tests/unit/execution/test_execution_safety.py:251:            assert plan.active_cycle is not None\n./backend/tests/unit/execution/test_execution_safety.py:252:            old_cycle = plan.active_cycle\n./backend/tests/unit/execution/test_execution_safety.py:289:    assert old_cycle.goals[0].tasks[0].status == Status.SKIPPED\n./frontend/src/lib/queries.ts:89:  PlanPhase,\n./frontend/src/lib/queries.ts:665:            const to = payload.to_phase as PlanPhase;\n./docs/history/analyses/2026-07-20-api-walkthrough-findings.md:28:**Root cause:** `ExecutionHandler.handle()` calls `_reserve_goal_promotion` for a\n./docs/history/analyses/2026-07-20-api-walkthrough-findings.md:34:(`_reserve_goal_promotion`, `:706`) raises `TaskFailed`. With no handler it\n./docs/history/analyses/2026-07-20-api-walkthrough-findings.md:72:the cyclic authority (`status == RUNNING and active_cycle is not None`) rather\n./docs/history/analyses/2026-07-20-api-walkthrough-findings.md:84:transaction safety (`_reserve_goal_promotion` is validation-first — it raises\n./docs/history/analyses/2026-07-20-api-walkthrough-findings.md:91:**terminal and none failed**, while `_reserve_goal_promotion` additionally\n./docs/history/analyses/2026-07-20-api-walkthrough-findings.md:138:Findings #2/#4/#5 all point to (guard on cyclic `status`/`active_cycle`, not\n./docs/history/analyses/2026-07-20-api-walkthrough-findings.md:307:and `Plan.begin_replanning` now consult the cyclic authority (`active_cycle` /\n./docs/history/analyses/2026-07-20-api-walkthrough-findings.md:308:`status`) instead of only the legacy `PlanPhase`, exactly as `resume()` already\n./docs/history/analyses/2026-07-20-api-walkthrough-findings.md:326:  `begin_replanning` sets `paused=False` but the following `resolve_block`\n./docs/history/analyses/2026-07-20-api-walkthrough-findings.md:338:**Root theme:** `request_replan` uses the legacy `begin_replanning` +\n./docs/history/analyses/2026-07-20-api-walkthrough-findings.md:350:#10 fixes both: `begin_replanning` now establishes the explicit WAITING replan\n./docs/history/analyses/2026-07-20-api-walkthrough-findings.md:352:resolves the block BEFORE `begin_replanning` so WAITING is the atomic final word;\n./docs/history/analyses/2026-07-20-api-walkthrough-findings.md:354:reports `replan_discovery`. Legacy (`active_cycle is None`) plans are byte-identical.\n./docs/history/analyses/2026-07-20-api-walkthrough-findings.md:363:14-item legacy-`PlanPhase` side-effect audit is tracked as follow-up cleanup.\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_cyclic_project_plan.py:122:    assert plan.active_cycle is active\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_cyclic_project_plan.py:142:    assert plan.active_cycle is None\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_cyclic_project_plan.py:146:def test_replan_activation_atomically_supersedes_active_cycle():\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_cyclic_project_plan.py:175:    assert plan.active_cycle is new_cycle\n./docs/history/analyses/2026-07-21-replan-recovery-domain-design-codex-sol.md:15:active_cycle=<active>\n./docs/history/analyses/2026-07-21-replan-recovery-domain-design-codex-sol.md:20:The immediate cause is ordering. `begin_replanning()` calls `_set_phase(REPLANNING)`, temporarily mapping the status to `WAITING` ([planner_orchestrator.py:469](backend/src/domain/aggregates/planner_orchestrator.py:469)), but `request_replan()` subsequently resolves the block ([request_replan.py:22](backend/src/app/use_cases/request_replan.py:22)). Generic `resolve_block()` then overwrites the status with `PAUSED` merely because an active cycle exists, without setting `paused=True` ([planner_orchestrator.py:833](backend/src/domain/aggregates/planner_orchestrator.py:833)).\n./docs/history/analyses/2026-07-21-replan-recovery-domain-design-codex-sol.md:22:Finding #13 is the artifact counterpart. `begin_replanning()` clears the manual pause and changes the legacy phase, but does not retire the current `intent_proposal`, `cycle_draft`, or `review_gate` slots ([planner_orchestrator.py:469](backend/src/domain/aggregates/planner_orchestrator.py:469)). An approved proposal is particularly harmful:\n./docs/history/analyses/2026-07-21-replan-recovery-domain-design-codex-sol.md:37:active_cycle       = existing source cycle\n./docs/history/analyses/2026-07-21-replan-recovery-domain-design-codex-sol.md:53:active_cycle       = unchanged source cycle\n./docs/history/analyses/2026-07-21-replan-recovery-domain-design-codex-sol.md:61:`begin_replanning()` should not fabricate an empty `IntentProposal`: the entity requires an objective and other reasoner-derived content ([planning_artifacts.py:99](backend/src/domain/entities/planning_artifacts.py:99)). It should open the *slot* for a fresh proposal by clearing stale current-artifact pointers. The conversation use case should continue constructing the actual `ProposalKind.REPLAN`, binding it to `active_cycle.id`, and opening its exact-revision gate when a candidate exists ([conversation.py:271](backend/src/app/use_cases/conversation.py:271)).\n./docs/history/analyses/2026-07-21-replan-recovery-domain-design-codex-sol.md:65:## Legacy `PlanPhase` side-effect audit\n./docs/history/analyses/2026-07-21-replan-recovery-domain-design-codex-sol.md:69:1. `_set_phase()` mutates both the compatibility projection and authoritative root status ([planner_orchestrator.py:144](backend/src/domain/aggregates/planner_orchestrator.py:144)). This is the central dual-authority hazard. Any cyclic compatibility update can silently overwrite a carefully selected status. It happens in `begin_replanning`, `retry_agent_binding`, planning enrichment, and activation.\n./docs/history/analyses/2026-07-21-replan-recovery-domain-design-codex-sol.md:83:8. `begin_replanning()` still sets root status indirectly through `_set_phase(REPLANNING)` ([planner_orchestrator.py:469](backend/src/domain/aggregates/planner_orchestrator.py:469)). Finding #12 demonstrates why relying on that incidental mapping is unsafe.\n./docs/history/analyses/2026-07-21-replan-recovery-domain-design-codex-sol.md:85:9. `commit_replanned_goals()` is guarded and advanced entirely by `PlanPhase`, writes legacy root `goals`, increments legacy `iteration`, and calls `_set_phase(ARCHITECTURE)` ([planner_orchestrator.py:517](backend/src/domain/aggregates/planner_orchestrator.py:517)). It is valid only for the legacy loop. Calling it from the cyclic conversation path would bypass `IntentProposal → ReviewGate → CycleDraft → ReviewGate → Cycle` and make the plan prematurely worker-claimable.\n./docs/history/analyses/2026-07-21-replan-recovery-domain-design-codex-sol.md:99:1. Deliberately record a narrow domain unfreeze for the cyclic replan consistency invariant. Scope it only to `begin_replanning`, `request_replan`, derived activity/actions, and regression tests. Do not use this fix as an opportunity to remove `PlanPhase` globally.\n./docs/history/analyses/2026-07-21-replan-recovery-domain-design-codex-sol.md:101:2. Split `Plan.begin_replanning()` behavior by lifecycle family at [planner_orchestrator.py:469](backend/src/domain/aggregates/planner_orchestrator.py:469):\n./docs/history/analyses/2026-07-21-replan-recovery-domain-design-codex-sol.md:103:   - Preserve the existing legacy branch byte-for-byte when `active_cycle is None`: retain the `{RUNNING, REVIEW}` phase guard, legacy root-goal skipping, pause clearing, and `_set_phase(REPLANNING)`.\n./docs/history/analyses/2026-07-21-replan-recovery-domain-design-codex-sol.md:104:   - For `active_cycle is not None`, make the cyclic postcondition explicit: clear manual pause fields and `pause_requested`; set the compatibility `phase` to `REPLANNING`; set `status=WAITING` directly; clear the current `intent_proposal`, `cycle_draft`, and `review_gate` slots; retain the active source cycle.\n./docs/history/analyses/2026-07-21-replan-recovery-domain-design-codex-sol.md:114:   - Invoke `begin_replanning()` after block resolution so its explicit `WAITING` postcondition is the transaction’s final lifecycle decision.\n./docs/history/analyses/2026-07-21-replan-recovery-domain-design-codex-sol.md:134:7. Keep cyclic conversation proposal creation where it is. `_conversation_turn()` should continue creating a fresh `ProposalKind.REPLAN` from the reasoner candidate, setting `source_cycle_id` from the still-active source cycle, and opening a new intent review gate atomically ([conversation.py:271](backend/src/app/use_cases/conversation.py:271)). No call to legacy `commit_replanned_goals()` should be introduced.\n./docs/history/analyses/2026-07-21-replan-recovery-domain-design-codex-sol.md:139:   - Extend `test_cyclic_plan_can_begin_replanning_with_replanning_legacy_phase` with the complete tuple invariant and stale approved-intent fixture ([test_cyclic_pause_replan_phase_guards.py:39](backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_cyclic_pause_replan_phase_guards.py:39)).\n./docs/history/analyses/2026-07-21-replan-recovery-domain-design-codex-sol.md:140:   - Retain the legacy rejection tests at [test_cyclic_pause_replan_phase_guards.py:47](backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_cyclic_pause_replan_phase_guards.py:47) and legacy replan-loop tests at [test_replan_loop.py:70](backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_replan_loop.py:70) to prove the `active_cycle is None` path remains unchanged.\n./docs/history/analyses/2026-07-21-replan-recovery-domain-design-codex-sol.md:144:The smallest safe correction is therefore: make cyclic `begin_replanning()` explicitly establish the `WAITING` conversational tuple, resolve a block before establishing that tuple, clear stale current planning artifacts without fabricating a proposal, and ensure the derived UI contract never advertises manual resume unless the manual pause flag is truly armed.\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_transitions.py:57:    t.skip()\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_transitions.py:58:    assert t.status == Status.SKIPPED\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_transitions.py:72:        (Status.SKIPPED, \"start\"),\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_transitions.py:113:@pytest.mark.parametrize(\"status\", [Status.PENDING, Status.RUNNING, Status.FAILED, Status.SKIPPED])\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_transitions.py:125:    assert t.status == Status.SKIPPED\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_transitions.py:128:@pytest.mark.parametrize(\"status\", [Status.DONE, Status.SKIPPED, Status.FAILED])\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_transitions.py:144:    g.skip()\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_transitions.py:145:    assert g.status == Status.SKIPPED\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_transitions.py:153:        g.skip()  # cannot skip a goal out from under a live task\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_transitions.py:155:    g.skip()  # all tasks terminal -> the finalize-abandon path may close it\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_transitions.py:156:    assert g.status == Status.SKIPPED\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_transitions.py:159:@pytest.mark.parametrize(\"status\", [Status.DONE, Status.SKIPPED, Status.FAILED])\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_transitions.py:163:        g.skip()\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_cyclic_worker.py:89:    goal = enriched.active_cycle.goals[0]  # type: ignore[union-attr]\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_cyclic_worker.py:90:    assert enriched.active_cycle is not None\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_cyclic_worker.py:91:    assert enriched.active_cycle.id == cycle.id\n./docs/history/analyses/2026-07-13-runtime-neutral-telemetry-architecture.md:35:- [`Plan`](../../../backend/src/domain/aggregates/planner_orchestrator.py) is the aggregate root. `PlanPhase` defines nine lifecycle phases, while `Plan.pause()`, `Plan.resume()`, task-start, task-result, and goal-completion methods enforce transitions. The aggregate stores planning backoff and pause state, but no provider, trace, token, cost, or telemetry state.\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_replan_loop.py:10:from src.domain.aggregates.planner_orchestrator import Plan, PlanPhase\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_replan_loop.py:85:        phase=PlanPhase.RUNNING,\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_replan_loop.py:92:    assert saved.phase == PlanPhase.REPLANNING\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_replan_loop.py:93:    assert saved.goals[1].status == Status.SKIPPED  # pending goal skipped\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_replan_loop.py:94:    assert saved.goals[1].tasks[0].status == Status.SKIPPED\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_replan_loop.py:97:    assert saved.goals[0].tasks[2].status == Status.SKIPPED  # its pending work skipped\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_replan_loop.py:106:        phase=PlanPhase.REVIEW,\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_replan_loop.py:111:    assert repo.get(\"p1\").phase == PlanPhase.REPLANNING\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_replan_loop.py:118:        PlanPhase.DISCOVERY,\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_replan_loop.py:119:        PlanPhase.ARCHITECTURE,\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_replan_loop.py:120:        PlanPhase.ENRICHING,\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_replan_loop.py:121:        PlanPhase.AWAITING_REVIEW,\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_replan_loop.py:122:        PlanPhase.REPLANNING,\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_replan_loop.py:133:def test_commit_replanned_goals_appends_bumps_iteration_and_flows_to_architecture():\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_replan_loop.py:136:        project_id=\"project-1\", id=\"p1\", brief=\"b\", phase=PlanPhase.REVIEW, goals=[done_goal]\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_replan_loop.py:147:        p.commit_replanned_goals(new_goals)\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_replan_loop.py:152:    assert saved.phase == PlanPhase.ARCHITECTURE\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_replan_loop.py:165:        project_id=\"project-1\", id=\"p1\", brief=\"b\", phase=PlanPhase.RUNNING, goals=[leftover]\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_replan_loop.py:172:        p.commit_replanned_goals(\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_replan_loop.py:179:    assert saved.goals[0].status == Status.SKIPPED  # finalize-abandon closed it\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_replan_loop.py:180:    assert saved.goals[0].tasks[0].status == Status.SKIPPED  # in-flight abandoned\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_replan_loop.py:188:    plan = Plan(project_id=\"project-1\", id=\"p1\", brief=\"b\", phase=PlanPhase.RUNNING)\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_replan_loop.py:190:        plan.commit_replanned_goals([])\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_replan_loop.py:214:        phase=PlanPhase.RUNNING,\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_replan_loop.py:227:    assert saved.goals[0].tasks[0].status == Status.SKIPPED  # terminal-skip\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_replan_loop.py:237:    assert saved.phase == PlanPhase.REPLANNING\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_replan_loop.py:238:    assert saved.goals[0].tasks[0].status == Status.SKIPPED\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_replan_loop.py:254:                p.commit_replanned_goals([Goal(id=\"n1\", name=\"n1\", position=0, description=\"\")])\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_replan_loop.py:263:    assert saved.goals[0].tasks[0].status == Status.SKIPPED  # stays closed\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_replan_loop.py:272:    plan = Plan(project_id=\"project-1\", id=\"p1\", brief=\"b\", phase=PlanPhase.REVIEW, goals=[done])\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_replan_loop.py:282:# ===== set_iteration_goals (the planning phases' write path) =====\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_replan_loop.py:283:def test_set_iteration_goals_replaces_pending_keeps_history():\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_replan_loop.py:290:        phase=PlanPhase.ARCHITECTURE,\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_replan_loop.py:293:    plan.set_iteration_goals(\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_replan_loop.py:307:        PlanPhase.AWAITING_REVIEW,\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_replan_loop.py:308:        PlanPhase.RUNNING,\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_replan_loop.py:309:        PlanPhase.REVIEW,\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_replan_loop.py:310:        PlanPhase.REPLANNING,\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_replan_loop.py:311:        PlanPhase.DONE,\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_replan_loop.py:314:def test_set_iteration_goals_only_in_planning_phases(phase):\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_replan_loop.py:317:        plan.set_iteration_goals([])\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_use_cases.py:8:from src.domain.aggregates.planner_orchestrator import Plan, PlanPhase\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_use_cases.py:93:    assert created.phase == PlanPhase.DISCOVERY\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_use_cases.py:132:        project_id=\"project-1\", id=\"p1\", brief=\"b\", phase=PlanPhase.AWAITING_REVIEW, goals=[g]\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_use_cases.py:227:    plan.phase = PlanPhase.RUNNING\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_use_cases.py:313:    plan.phase = PlanPhase.RUNNING  # not paused\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_use_cases.py:355:def test_blocked_cyclic_edit_targets_the_active_cycle_without_manual_pause():\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_use_cases.py:370:    plan.phase = PlanPhase.RUNNING\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_use_cases.py:389:    assert saved.active_cycle is not None\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_use_cases.py:390:    assert saved.active_cycle.goals[0].tasks[0].description == \"recovered\"\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_use_cases.py:391:    assert saved.active_cycle.goals[0].tasks[0].revision == 2\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_use_cases.py:414:    assert repo.get(\"p1\").phase == PlanPhase.RUNNING\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_use_cases.py:419:    plan.phase = PlanPhase.RUNNING\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_use_cases.py:427:    plan.phase = PlanPhase.RUNNING\n./docs/architecture/plan-lifecycle.md:161:`PlanPhase`, legacy conversation routes, and root `goals` remain a\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_execution_handler_unpromotable_goal.py:5:signal. `_reserve_goal_promotion` additionally requires every task be DONE\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_execution_handler_unpromotable_goal.py:30:from src.domain.aggregates.planner_orchestrator import Plan, PlanPhase\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_execution_handler_unpromotable_goal.py:64:        phase=PlanPhase.RUNNING,\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_execution_handler_unpromotable_goal.py:93:    still_open_goal = blocked.active_cycle.goals[0]  # type: ignore[union-attr]\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_cyclic_pause_replan_phase_guards.py:7:from src.domain.aggregates.planner_orchestrator import Plan, PlanPhase\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_cyclic_pause_replan_phase_guards.py:25:    plan._set_phase(PlanPhase.REPLANNING)\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_cyclic_pause_replan_phase_guards.py:39:def test_cyclic_plan_can_begin_replanning_with_replanning_legacy_phase() -> None:\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_cyclic_pause_replan_phase_guards.py:42:    plan.begin_replanning()\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_cyclic_pause_replan_phase_guards.py:44:    assert plan.phase == PlanPhase.REPLANNING\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_cyclic_pause_replan_phase_guards.py:47:def test_legacy_plan_cannot_begin_replanning_from_replanning() -> None:\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_cyclic_pause_replan_phase_guards.py:48:    plan = Plan(id=\"plan-1\", brief=\"brief\", phase=PlanPhase.REPLANNING)\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_cyclic_pause_replan_phase_guards.py:51:        plan.begin_replanning()\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_cyclic_pause_replan_phase_guards.py:55:    plan = Plan(id=\"plan-1\", brief=\"brief\", phase=PlanPhase.REPLANNING)\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_cyclic_pause_replan_phase_guards.py:77:def test_cyclic_begin_replanning_lands_in_waiting_replan_discovery() -> None:\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_cyclic_pause_replan_phase_guards.py:78:    # Unfreeze #10: begin_replanning on a cyclic plan lands in the coherent\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_cyclic_pause_replan_phase_guards.py:82:    plan.begin_replanning()\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_cyclic_pause_replan_phase_guards.py:86:    assert plan.active_cycle is not None\n./docs/architecture/known-issues.md:9:- `PlanPhase`, the legacy conversation/control routes, and root `goals`\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_backoff_gate.py:10:from src.domain.aggregates.planner_orchestrator import Plan, PlanPhase\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_backoff_gate.py:35:        phase=PlanPhase.RUNNING,\n./docs/architecture/overview.md:91:`PlanPhase` now serves legacy compatibility only. Current authority is the\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_agent_binding_recovery.py:6:from src.domain.aggregates.planner_orchestrator import Plan, PlanPhase\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_agent_binding_recovery.py:35:        phase=PlanPhase.ENRICHING,\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_agent_binding_recovery.py:95:    assert stored.phase == PlanPhase.RUNNING\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_agent_binding_recovery.py:97:    rebound = stored.active_cycle.goals[0].tasks\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_agent_binding_recovery.py:122:    for task in stored.active_cycle.goals[0].tasks:\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_advance_plan.py:10:from src.domain.aggregates.planner_orchestrator import Plan, PlanPhase\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_advance_plan.py:41:        phase=PlanPhase.RUNNING,\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_advance_plan.py:59:    if signal == \"paused\" and env.stored(\"p1\").phase == PlanPhase.REVIEW:\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_advance_plan.py:71:    assert final.phase == PlanPhase.DONE\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_advance_plan.py:111:    assert final.phase == PlanPhase.RUNNING and final.paused\n./docs/history/planning/2026-07-14-cyclic-project-plan-implementation.md:13:| Aggregate/lifecycle | `planner_orchestrator.Plan`, `PlanPhase` | project binding, root status, cycles, versioned review artifacts, blocks, graceful pause |\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_conversation_and_planning.py:16:from src.domain.aggregates.planner_orchestrator import Plan, PlanPhase\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_conversation_and_planning.py:43:def plan_in(phase: PlanPhase, goals: list[Goal] | None = None) -> Plan:\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_conversation_and_planning.py:89:    env.seed(plan_in(PlanPhase.DISCOVERY))\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_conversation_and_planning.py:96:    assert result.phase == PlanPhase.DISCOVERY\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_conversation_and_planning.py:97:    assert env.stored(\"p1\").phase == PlanPhase.DISCOVERY  # nothing advanced\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_conversation_and_planning.py:110:    env.seed(plan_in(PlanPhase.DISCOVERY))\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_conversation_and_planning.py:130:    assert (result.committed, result.phase) == (True, PlanPhase.DISCOVERY)\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_conversation_and_planning.py:151:    env.seed(plan_in(PlanPhase.AWAITING_REVIEW, [old]))\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_conversation_and_planning.py:159:    assert env.stored(\"p1\").phase == PlanPhase.DISCOVERY\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_conversation_and_planning.py:174:    assert (result.committed, result.phase) == (True, PlanPhase.DISCOVERY)\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_conversation_and_planning.py:185:    env.seed(plan_in(PlanPhase.DISCOVERY))\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_conversation_and_planning.py:197:    assert env.stored(\"p1\").phase == PlanPhase.DISCOVERY\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_conversation_and_planning.py:206:    env.seed(plan_in(PlanPhase.RUNNING, [goal(\"g1\", 0, [task(\"t1\")])]))\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_conversation_and_planning.py:222:    plan = plan_in(PlanPhase.REPLANNING)\n.