     plan.advance_phase(PlanPhase.DISCOVERY)  # any non-ENRICHING phase\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_worker_loop.py:11:from src.domain.aggregates.planner_orchestrator import Plan, PlanPhase\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_worker_loop.py:39:    return Plan(project_id=\"project-1\", id=\"p1\", brief=\"b\", phase=PlanPhase.RUNNING, goals=[g1, g2])\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_worker_loop.py:50:    assert final.phase == PlanPhase.REVIEW\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_worker_loop.py:53:    assert env.stored(\"p1\").phase == PlanPhase.DONE\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_worker_loop.py:91:    assert mid.phase == PlanPhase.RUNNING\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_worker_loop.py:102:    assert final.phase == PlanPhase.REVIEW  # execution exhausted -> post-exec gate\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_worker_loop.py:114:        PlanPhase.DISCOVERY,\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_worker_loop.py:115:        PlanPhase.REPLANNING,\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_worker_loop.py:116:        PlanPhase.AWAITING_REVIEW,\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_worker_loop.py:117:        PlanPhase.REVIEW,\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_worker_loop.py:118:        PlanPhase.DONE,\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_worker_loop.py:119:        PlanPhase.FAILED,\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_worker_loop.py:125:    for i, phase in enumerate([PlanPhase.ARCHITECTURE, PlanPhase.ENRICHING, PlanPhase.RUNNING]):\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_worker_loop.py:134:    env.seed(Plan(project_id=\"project-1\", id=\"p1\", brief=\"b\", phase=PlanPhase.RUNNING))\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_worker_loop.py:145:    env.seed(Plan(project_id=\"project-1\", id=\"p1\", brief=\"b\", phase=PlanPhase.RUNNING))\n./docs/decisions/decision-log.md:14:6. **Mid-RUNNING replan abandons in-flight work**: PENDING goals/tasks are SKIPPED at request time; the in-flight task finalizes tolerantly; commit-time finalize-abandon closes the rest (the \"resurrection bug\" fix — a stale goal must never re-execute after the next iteration starts).\n./docs/decisions/decision-log.md:76:    - **Reopen-discovery.** New guarded `reopen_discovery()` (`AWAITING_REVIEW → DISCOVERY`, clears pause) for \"request changes\" at the pre-execution gate. The next commit flows through `set_iteration_goals`, which **replaces** the un-executed roadmap (terminal history kept) — distinct from REPLANNING, whose commit appends and bumps `iteration`.\n./docs/decisions/decision-log.md:77:    - **Strict in-goal order.** `next_action` now blocks a goal on its head (first non-terminal, position order) task: a backing-off head yields the whole goal instead of skipping ahead to a later task. Tasks in a goal are a sequential chain; cross-goal order is unchanged (position + `depends_on`). `begin_replanning()` also clears the pause gate so a committed re-plan can execute.\n./docs/decisions/decision-log.md:115:`Plan.request_pause`, `Plan.pause`, and `Plan.begin_replanning` guarded on the\n./docs/decisions/decision-log.md:116:legacy `PlanPhase` (`WORKER_CLAIMABLE_PHASES` / `{RUNNING, REVIEW}`), but a\n./docs/decisions/decision-log.md:123:is legal when `status == RUNNING` and (`active_cycle is not None` or the legacy\n./docs/decisions/decision-log.md:124:phase is claimable); `begin_replanning` skips the legacy phase guard when\n./docs/decisions/decision-log.md:125:`active_cycle is not None`. Legacy (pre-cyclic) plans keep the phase guards\n./docs/decisions/decision-log.md:130:state.** Findings #12/#13: `request_replan` composed `begin_replanning` (which\n./docs/decisions/decision-log.md:137:masqueraded as active planning work. Fix: (a) `begin_replanning` on a cyclic plan\n./docs/decisions/decision-log.md:140:source `Cycle` (legacy `active_cycle is None` plans byte-identical); (b)\n./docs/decisions/decision-log.md:141:`request_replan` resolves the block BEFORE `begin_replanning` so the WAITING\n./docs/decisions/decision-log.md:148:A codex `gpt-5.6-sol` design analysis (with a 14-item legacy-`PlanPhase`\n./docs/history/planning/2026-07-02-master-roadmap-final-fable-5.md:87:triggers a replan mid-execution, incomplete goals are **SKIPPED** (not finished first);\n./docs/history/planning/2026-07-02-master-roadmap-final-fable-5.md:125:tasks, then close the goal as SKIPPED. Late in-flight results: success finalizes\n./docs/history/planning/2026-07-02-master-roadmap-final-fable-5.md:159:- [ ] **🐛 Add `Goal.skip()` (verified missing):** the decided \"skip incomplete goals\"\n./docs/history/planning/2026-07-02-master-roadmap-final-fable-5.md:565:    requeue into an abandoned iteration. `Goal.skip()` added to the domain.\n./frontend/src/types/ui.ts:50:export type PlanPhase =\n./frontend/src/types/ui.ts:216:  active_cycle: ActiveCycle | null;\n./frontend/src/types/ui.ts:223:  phase: PlanPhase;\n./frontend/src/types/ui.ts:238:  phase: PlanPhase;\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_execution_records.py:15:from src.domain.aggregates.planner_orchestrator import Plan, PlanPhase\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_execution_records.py:29:        phase=PlanPhase.RUNNING,\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_execution_records.py:266:    assert stored.active_cycle is not None\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_execution_records.py:267:    assert stored.active_cycle.goals[0].tasks[1].status == Status.PENDING\n./backend/tests/unit/reasoner/test_context.py:8:from src.domain.aggregates.planner_orchestrator import Plan, PlanPhase\n./backend/tests/unit/reasoner/test_context.py:48:        phase=PlanPhase.REPLANNING,\n./docs/history/planning/2026-07-03-working-prototype-reasoner-frontend-fable-5.md:60:**`src/app/use_cases/conversation.py`**: both message use cases return `ConversationResult(reply, committed, phase)`. Flow: guard phase → persist the **user** message BEFORE the LLM call → `reasoner.converse(...)` outside any txn → if `goals is None`: append assistant reply (`meta committed=false`), phase unchanged; else re-open txn, re-guard, `set_iteration_goals`+`advance_phase(ARCHITECTURE)` (discovery) / `commit_replanned_goals` (replanning), bump, `PhaseAdvanced` outbox, save; append assistant reply (`meta committed=true`).\n./docs/history/planning/2026-07-03-working-prototype-reasoner-frontend-fable-5.md:74:2. if target: `tasks = await reasoner.enrich_goal(plan, target, capabilities.list())` (LLM outside txn) → re-open txn, re-guard phase, re-find goal by id — **if it now has tasks, no-op** (idempotency, the old JIT guard) — else rebuild the non-terminal goal list with the target's tasks set, `set_iteration_goals`, bump, save → `Signal.CONTINUE` (the between-goals crash checkpoint);\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_pause_resume.py:15:from src.domain.aggregates.planner_orchestrator import Plan, PlanPhase\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_pause_resume.py:49:        phase=PlanPhase.RUNNING,\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_pause_resume.py:113:    plan.phase = PlanPhase.AWAITING_REVIEW  # gates are already paused by design\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_pause_resume.py:220:    retried = stored.active_cycle.goals[0].tasks[0]\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_pause_resume.py:271:    edited = env.stored(\"p1\").active_cycle.goals[0].tasks[0]\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_pause_resume.py:278:    continued = stored.active_cycle.goals[0].tasks[0]\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_pause_resume.py:345:    assert stored.active_cycle.goals[0].tasks[0].status == Status.PENDING\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_pause_resume.py:384:        phase=PlanPhase.ENRICHING,\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_pause_resume.py:422:    assert env.stored(\"p1\").phase == PlanPhase.REVIEW  # succeeded and exhausted scan\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_pause_resume.py:434:    assert stored.phase == PlanPhase.RUNNING and stored.paused\n./backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_pause_r